                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d762">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2156.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mexican Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 27, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 68.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 21st instant, in which you request that the proper authorities
                    of <pb facs="0590" n="508" xml:id="pg_508"/> San Pedro, Cal., be requested to
                    arrange to defeat the maneuvers of the Magonist Junta at Los Angeles toward
                    sending expeditions from that place to Lower California.</p>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to inform you that the Department of Justice has been
                    requested to take appropriate action in regard to the matter.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
